The paper deals with quantum interactive proof systems and their expressive power, which are topics typically studied in computer science theory. The use of quantum mechanics suggests a focus on quantum computing, leading to the likely sub-categories of cs.CC (computational complexity) and cs.QI (quantum information). The establishment of a quantum measurement also suggests a possible connection to information theory (cs.IT). The ellipsoid method for convex feasibility mentioned in the abstract is a common tool in optimization and computational geometry, suggesting the possible sub-categories of cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.LG (machine learning).
